# Maintainer: Oichkatzelesfrettschen
# Meta-package for complete IA-16 cross-compilation toolchain

pkgname=ia16-toolchain-custom
pkgver=1.0
pkgrel=1
pkgdesc="Complete IA-16 cross-compilation toolchain (meta-package)"
arch=('x86_64')
url="https://github.com/Oichkatzelesfrettschen"
license=('GPL-3.0-or-later')
depends=(
    'binutils-ia16-custom-git'
    'gcc-ia16-custom-git'
    'newlib-ia16-custom-git'
)
optdepends=(
    'bochs: 8086 emulator with debugger'
    '86box-git: Cycle-accurate x86 PC emulator'
    'qemu-system-x86: Quick testing (not true 8086)'
)

# This is a meta-package, nothing to build
package() {
    # Create directory for documentation
    install -d "${pkgdir}/usr/share/doc/${pkgname}"

    # Create a README
    cat > "${pkgdir}/usr/share/doc/${pkgname}/README" << 'EOF'
IA-16 Cross-Compilation Toolchain
==================================

This meta-package installs the complete IA-16 cross-compilation toolchain:

Components:
- binutils-ia16-custom-git: Assembler, linker, and binary utilities
- gcc-ia16-custom-git: GCC 6.3.0 C/C++ compiler for IA-16
- newlib-ia16-custom-git: C library for IA-16 targets

Installation Directory: /opt/ia16

Usage:
  export PATH=/opt/ia16/bin:$PATH
  ia16-elf-gcc -o hello.com hello.c

Target triplet: ia16-elf

Supported CPUs:
- Intel 8086/8088
- Intel 80186/80188
- Intel 80286
- NEC V20/V30

For more information, see:
https://github.com/Oichkatzelesfrettschen/gcc-ia16-8088-custom
EOF
}
